1)   $docker --version
------to check docker version
2)    $docker run hello-world
------ runs the hello-world image,if its not there in local repo it will pull from dockerhub
3)    $ docker run --detach --publish=80:80 --name=webserver nginx
In a web browser, go to http://localhost/ to view the nginx homepage. Because we specified the default HTTP port, it isnâ€™t necessary to append :80 at the end of the URL.
4)  docker ps/docker container ls
----displays running containers
5)  docker ps -a
-----to view all containers running and exited containers

